text: Kiruna Church () is a church building in the town of Kiruna in Sweden. It was built in the early 20th century. The church belongs to the Jukkasjärvi Parish of the Church of Sweden. It was opened on 8 December 1912 by bishop Olof Bergqvist. ==References== ==Other websites== *Jukkasjärvi Parish Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Kiruna
